  "title": " fix(numericSelector): make default value possible ",
  "body": "When we created the connectNumericSelector, we made sure to support `undefined` as a special value to unset the filters. However because the implementations are DOM based, the value is now a string. This patch fixes that (and adds the documentation to the feature)\r\n\r\nI also updated the example because it was super hard to maintain and didn't have much sense in terms of feature. The new example also show case the undefined value :)",
